<meta name="description" content="Native American Technology  &amp; Art: A topically organized educational web site emphasizing the Eastern Woodland Indians region, organized into categories of Beadwork, Birds &amp; Feathers, Clay &amp; Pottery, Leather &amp; Clothes, Metalwork, Plants &amp; Trees, Porcupine Quills, Stonework &amp; Tools, Weaving &amp; Cordage, Games &amp; Toys and Food &amp; Recipes. Instructional information about these materials, and background on the history and development of Native technologies.  Dedicated to disconnecting the term primitive from perceptions of Native American technology and art."> 
